where Ea is the activation energy, k is the Boltzmann constant, and a is a constant. Figure 12a displays the plotting of the emission intensity with respect to 1/T, where the value of activation energy (Ea) is calculated to be 0.329 ± 0.02 eV. In order to probe the reason for thermal quenching of CDs emission process, the radiative (Vr) and nonradiative (Vnr) recombination rates of CDs were determined from the lifetime (τ*) and quantum yield (QY) as:
